NATIONAL LABOR RELATIONS BOARD, Petitioner, v. ENGLISH FREIGHT COMPANY, Respondent. No. 11440. Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit Jan. 17, 1946. David A. Morse, Gen. Counsel, National Labor Relations Board, Malcolm F. Hal-liday, Associate Gen. Counsel, N.L.R.B., and Thurlow Smoot, Sr., Atty., N.L.R.B., all of Washington, D. C., for petitioner. No appearance for respondent.

Before SIBLEY, WALLER, and LEE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Let a decree be entered enforcing the order of the National Labor Relations Board set forth in the petition.
